What you need to know:

Since being drafted to the team for 2007 FIVB World Cup, Agala has proudly represented Kenya for 10 years until her untimely exit in 2016 ahead of the Rio Olympic qualifiers.The saying ‘the stone the builder rejected has become the corner stone’ perhaps best explains her journey to captaining the team. She is now a holder of FIVB Level Two coaching certificateKVF’s Most Valuable Player finds joy in team performances rather than individual accolades.Winning 2015 FIVB World Prix Group Three in Australia is one of her biggest moments